Agrofert is a Czech conglomerate holding company headquartered in Prague, Czech Republic. It operates agriculture, food, chemical, construction, logistics, forestry, energy and mass media industries in the European Union and China. It was founded in 1993 by businessman Andrej Babi≈°, and he was its sole owner until 2017. In the 2010s he began his involvement in politics, becoming Finance Minister of the Czech Republic in 2014. In 2017, with the adoption of new conflict of interest legislation he was forced to transfer ownership of company to trust funds controlled by his family and co-workers.


